{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51895318-d909-4c57-ac14-581315ce5f51","content":"`SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` tells the page not to add safe-area padding, but there are usually two other things still pushing your image inward:\n\n**1. Hide the app-level navigation/tab bars**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage ...\n    SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"\n    Shell.NavBarIsVisible=\"False\"\n    Shell.TabBarIsVisible=\"False\">\n```\n\nOr if using `NavigationPage`:\n```xml\nNavigationPage.HasNavigationBar=\"False\"\n```\n\n**2. Enable edge-to-edge drawing on Android**\n\nIn .NET 10, register the platform callback in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android.OnCreate((activity, _) =>\n    {\n        AndroidX.Core.View.WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(activity.Window!, false);\n    }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\nThis tells Android to let your content draw behind the status bar and navigation bar.\n\n**3. Make the image fill the space**\n\n```xml\n<Image Source=\"photo.jpg\"\n       Aspect=\"AspectFill\"\n       HorizontalOptions=\"Fill\"\n       VerticalOptions=\"Fill\" />\n```\n\nWithout `Aspect=\"AspectFill\"`, the image will letterbox itself and you'll see gaps even though the *page* is edge-to-edge.\n\n**iOS** generally works with just `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"`. If you also want to hide the iOS status bar, override it in your platform's `AppDelegate` or a custom page renderer.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7d317735-ede9-45fa-b3be-98b3e75ef69a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is working on a .NET MAUI app targeting .NET 10 and wants an image to go edge-to-edge (behind status bar and navigation bar), but setting `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the ContentPage isn't enough. Let me think about what's needed here.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, to achieve true edge-to-edge content that goes behind system bars, you need to:\n\n1. Set `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` on the page — this tells the page not to respect safe area insets.\n2. But more importantly, you also need to opt into edge-to-edge display mode. In .NET MAUI on .NET 9+, there's the concept of edge-to-edge / full-screen rendering.\n\n\n3. On Android specifically, edge-to-edge is now the default in .NET 10, but on iOS the safe area handling works differently, and individual views might need `IgnoreSafeArea` set to truly ignore the safe area insets. The real culprit is likely a NavigationPage or Shell wrapper adding its own padding, or on Android, the window not being configured to draw edge-to-edge—I should check if they need `Window.EdgeToEdge = true` in .NET 9 or if the Image's `Aspect` property needs to be set to `AspectFill` to actually fill the space. 10 MAUI, the most common issues for edge-to-edge:\n\n1. **Missing `Shell.NavBarIsVisible=\"False\"`** or **`NavigationPage.HasNavigationBar=\"False\"`** — This removes the app's navigation bar.\n\n2. **Not hiding the system status bar / navigation bar on the platform level** — On Android, you need to use immersive/full-screen mode. On iOS, you need to hide the status bar.\n\n3. **The `IgnoreSafeArea` property** — On individual layouts/views.\n\nFor .NET MAUI targeting .NET 10, the real issue is that `SafeAreaEdges=\"None\"` only handles safe area padding—it doesn't actually hide system bars or enable edge-to-edge rendering across platforms. Beyond that, I need to consider platform-specific implementations for immersive mode on Android, handle iOS safe area insets from the notch, hide the app navigation bar, and potentially set the image to fill the entire space. The real issue is likely that the page is wrapped in a Shell or NavigationPage adding its own chrome — I need to disable those with `Shell.NavBarIsVisible=\"False\"` and `Shell.TabBarIsVisible=\"False\"`. On Android, edge-to-edge rendering might need explicit configuration like `ConfigureAndroidEdgeToEdge()`, and on iOS I'd need to hide the status bar through platform-specific code. The image itself should also use `Aspect=\"AspectFill\"` to fill the space properly.","outputTokens":1986,"requestId":"77F7:18DC54:17EC63:1C9321:69EAC0A7"},"id":"5eebfc22-9367-4732-93c9-87836c167269","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:01:03.717Z","parentId":"40694568-cef0-42a5-aa14-521f02ca8ed3"}
